What are you doing?

220
00:18:15,006 --> 00:18:16,871
Keeping you right where I can see you.

221
00:18:17,041 --> 00:18:21,740
I'm not saying you're out of trouble yet.
At least you're with the good guys.

222
00:18:22,246 --> 00:18:24,908
Welcome to the quarantine express.

223
00:18:31,856 --> 00:18:35,952
All right, anybody here tattooed yet?
Because if you are, we cannot help you.

224
00:18:36,127 --> 00:18:37,253
No.

225
00:18:41,232 --> 00:18:42,563
Okay, pull out, Lennie.

226
00:18:44,935 --> 00:18:45,993
Willie, we're moving.

227
00:18:46,804 --> 00:18:49,466
Forty-five minutes,
they would have had you in quarantine.

228
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:50,868
You're safe now.

229
00:18:51,042 --> 00:18:54,478
Forget about going home because
that's the first place they're gonna look.

230
00:18:54,645 --> 00:18:57,011
-We just gotta get you out of here.
-And then what?

231
00:18:57,214 --> 00:19:01,048
-Not my department.
-We have safe houses.

232
00:19:01,252 --> 00:19:05,279
They're not the Hilton Hotel, but they're
better than where you were headed.

233
00:19:07,491 --> 00:19:09,982
Be careful not to breathe too deep
around these guys.

234
00:19:10,161 --> 00:19:13,460
-Can't you get it that way?
-Don't you read the government reports?

235
00:19:14,298 --> 00:19:16,789
Perplexing mystery.
Nobody knows for sure.

236
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:18,457
Isn't that what they said?

237
00:19:19,503 --> 00:19:23,269
The only way to get this disease
is straight into your bloodstream...

238
00:19:23,474 --> 00:19:24,634
...one way or another.

239
00:19:24,809 --> 00:19:27,937
I'm cold. I'm so cold.

240
00:19:28,245 --> 00:19:30,679
Can I call my grandma?
I want her to know I'm all right.

241
00:19:30,881 --> 00:19:34,578
No phone calls. We'll get a message
to her when it's safe.

242
00:19:38,689 --> 00:19:41,453
<i>There's cops behind you, a block away.</i>

243
00:19:41,625 --> 00:19:43,024
Lennie, move it.

244
00:19:46,297 --> 00:19:48,925
You took the wrong fucking ramp,
Lennie.

245
00:19:49,100 --> 00:19:52,900
-The wagons are on the other side.
-Well, what was he supposed to do?

246
00:20:03,414 --> 00:20:06,474
We'll never get across that.
Please tell me this isn't happening.

247
00:20:06,650 --> 00:20:09,050
<i>Don't even think</i>
<i>about going back down.</i>

248
00:20:09,220 --> 00:20:11,984
That cop's still sniffing around.

249
00:20:19,964 --> 00:20:21,022
Pack up the van.

250
00:20:24,702 --> 00:20:27,000
One hand right in front of the other.
That's right.

251
00:20:27,304 --> 00:20:29,067
You're doing great.

252
00:20:31,942 --> 00:20:34,467
Didn't know you had a date tonight.

253
00:20:35,613 --> 00:20:38,514
Wait over there. Over there.

254
00:20:38,716 --> 00:20:40,946
There you go. Okay.

255
00:20:41,152 --> 00:20:44,644
-All right, one hand in front of the other.
<i>-These cops keep hanging around.</i>

256
00:20:44,822 --> 00:20:46,084
<i>I don't get it, man.</i>

257
00:20:46,257 --> 00:20:49,226
<i>-You lost that other guy, I know you did.</i>
-Right across.

258
00:20:49,393 --> 00:20:50,451
Lennie, pull out!

259
00:20:54,932 --> 00:20:56,763
Don't move.

260
00:21:00,771 --> 00:21:03,501
<i>Come on, man. Come on, move it.</i>

261
00:21:12,416 --> 00:21:14,714
-Get back.
-Don't be crazy.

262
00:21:14,885 --> 00:21:16,682
Come on.

263
00:21:24,595 --> 00:21:27,462
<i>We got trouble, man.</i>
<i>There's a cop coming down Pavonia.</i>

264
00:21:27,898 --> 00:21:30,196
<i>He's headed straight for us, Torch.</i>

265
00:21:30,401 --> 00:21:33,768
<i>They must have some kind</i>
<i>of tracking thing in the van.</i>

266
00:21:33,938 --> 00:21:37,931
Don't listen to him.
Walk when I walk, okay?

267
00:21:45,082 --> 00:21:46,743
Okay.

268
00:21:56,961 --> 00:21:58,861
Oh, my God.

269
00:21:59,730 --> 00:22:02,858
-Oh, my God.
-Just get up very slowly.

270
00:22:07,338 --> 00:22:09,238
No, I can't move.

271
00:22:10,207 --> 00:22:13,665
Guess you'd rather stick around
and wait for the bomb to go off.

272
00:22:14,478 --> 00:22:15,536
What bomb?

273
00:22:15,713 --> 00:22:18,910
What did you think I was doing
back there, setting my alarm clock?

274
00:22:20,985 --> 00:22:25,217
Don't look down. Look at me.

275
00:22:26,323 --> 00:22:28,917
It's gonna break.
The ladder's gonna break.

276
00:22:30,261 --> 00:22:31,922
-What's your name?
-What?

277
00:22:32,096 --> 00:22:33,723
I asked you what your name was.

278
00:22:34,765 --> 00:22:38,496
-Blue.
-Don't look down. Look at me.

279
00:22:39,169 --> 00:22:41,603
Look in my eyes, Blue.

280
00:22:41,772 --> 00:22:43,933
Don't look down. Look in my eyes.

281
00:22:44,875 --> 00:22:47,309
Just get up very slowly.

282
00:22:54,285 --> 00:22:57,777
You can trust me or you can die.

283
00:23:05,362 --> 00:23:07,296
That's it. That's it. Okay.

284
00:23:07,865 --> 00:23:11,198
You're gonna be okay, Blue.
Ain't got nothing to worry about.

285
00:23:11,368 --> 00:23:13,962
Me, I'm telling you...

286
00:23:14,271 --> 00:23:18,298
...when I go, it ain't gonna be
from falling off no fucking ladder.

287
00:23:21,312 --> 00:23:22,574
<i>Come on, you guys.</i>

288
00:23:33,324 --> 00:23:34,621
Give me your hand. Come on!

289
00:23:35,492 --> 00:23:37,551
Come on.

290
00:23:38,295 --> 00:23:40,820
Give me your hand. Come on.

291
00:23:50,374 --> 00:23:52,535
Hands up! Now!

292
00:23:54,311 --> 00:23:55,938
Call for backup.

293
00:23:56,246 --> 00:23:57,508
Why bother?

294
00:23:57,681 --> 00:24:01,276
-We have the authority for this?
-Are you gonna give me trouble?

295
00:24:01,452 --> 00:24:03,420
I don't know about this, man.

296
00:24:03,587 --> 00:24:05,646
All you need to know
is that we got orders.

297
00:24:07,791 --> 00:24:09,520
Yes!

298
00:24:10,728 --> 00:24:12,923
Okay. Okay, easy with this guy.

299
00:24:13,230 --> 00:24:15,596
Okay, I got him.

300
00:24:32,716 --> 00:24:34,115
Do you do this every night?

301
00:24:38,622 --> 00:24:40,249
What are you doing?

302
00:24:40,424 --> 00:24:43,791
You'd better wear a blindfold
till we get where we're going.

303
00:24:45,362 --> 00:24:47,592
I'm not putting this disgusting thing
on my face.

304
00:24:47,798 --> 00:24:49,493
There are doctors where we're going.

305
00:24:49,666 --> 00:24:54,535
Food. Beds. You don't put that on,
they don't get there.

306
00:25:20,697 --> 00:25:23,188
Willie, sit them down over there.

307
00:25:25,569 --> 00:25:26,593
Make it comfortable.

308
00:25:26,770 --> 00:25:28,795
Help me get this guy
a wheelchair, okay?

309
00:25:41,585 --> 00:25:45,851
-Where are we?
-Someplace they don't know about yet.

310
00:25:51,395 --> 00:25:53,829
-What happened to him?
-I don't know.

311
00:25:54,264 --> 00:25:56,494
Okay, bring him over here.

312
00:25:57,768 --> 00:26:00,362
Bring him down real careful.

313
00:26:00,537 --> 00:26:02,903
Okay. Now,
you just hang in there, Stu.

314
00:26:03,207 --> 00:26:05,198
We'll make you
as comfortable as you can be.

315
00:26:05,409 --> 00:26:09,209
-You'll let my son know I'm all right?
-Just hold real steady.

316
00:26:11,815 --> 00:26:12,907
You okay?

317
00:26:13,083 --> 00:26:15,574
You'd think it would get a little easier
after a while.

318
00:26:15,752 --> 00:26:18,220
You are really sick.
There's some medicine.

319
00:26:18,622 --> 00:26:21,147
Stuff we smuggle in from New York.

320
00:26:21,358 --> 00:26:22,552
-Lennie.
-Yeah.

321
00:26:22,726 --> 00:26:24,921
Take her home now.

322
00:26:28,332 --> 00:26:30,357
Where am I taking you?

323
00:26:30,567 --> 00:26:33,035
1 4 West 90th Street.

324
00:26:59,196 --> 00:27:00,663
Yeah, Hunter...

325
00:27:00,831 --> 00:27:03,800
...she clocked in at 6:03.

326
00:27:07,571 --> 00:27:10,096
I don't wanna hear about it.

327
00:27:10,707 --> 00:27:11,969
Me either.

328
00:27:12,876 --> 00:27:15,504
I wanna hear about this.

329
00:27:16,847 --> 00:27:20,305
I don't get it.
Did Laurie get tested or didn't she?

330
00:27:20,484 --> 00:27:23,544
-Why are you going through my things?
-Where did you get this from?

331
00:27:23,720 --> 00:27:27,588
Stop the presses. I'm only gonna be
a half-hour late for work today.

332
00:27:29,459 --> 00:27:31,518
Did you have a good run?

333
00:27:32,196 --> 00:27:35,290
Mom's really impressed that
you've taken up early morning jogging.

334
00:27:35,465 --> 00:27:38,628
Oh, yeah, yeah, it's great.
You know, it really gets the blood going.

335
00:27:38,802 --> 00:27:42,795
I don't have blood anymore.
I just have coffee.

336
00:27:42,973 --> 00:27:44,338
You should eat something, Mom.

337
00:27:45,375 --> 00:27:46,808
Thanks.

338
00:27:49,279 --> 00:27:51,406
What's going on, Blue?

339
00:27:52,950 --> 00:27:54,747
Bucky...

340
00:27:56,386 --> 00:27:59,321
...you know the stuff they keep
telling us about the quarantine?

341
00:27:59,489 --> 00:28:02,356
How great it's supposed to be,
all clean and happy and wonderful?

342
00:28:02,559 --> 00:28:05,084
-Yeah.
-It's all lies.

343
00:28:05,262 --> 00:28:07,822
They lock these people up,
they don't give them medicine--

344
00:28:08,098 --> 00:28:10,225
They won't let their families
visit them?

345
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:13,597
The quarantine has to be total.
It's too much of a risk.

346
00:28:13,770 --> 00:28:16,705
Why can't they talk to anybody
on the telephone? Tell me that.

347
00:28:16,873 --> 00:28:18,773
You tell me where you were last night.

348
00:28:20,744 --> 00:28:23,577
Listen to this. You have to hear this.

349
00:28:23,747 --> 00:28:26,272
<i>Authorities attribute the hijacking</i>
<i>of the ambulance...</i>

350
00:28:26,450 --> 00:28:29,214
<i>...to an unnamed group</i>
<i>intent on causing panic in the city.</i>

351
00:28:29,386 --> 00:28:32,219
<i>No suspects have been arrested,</i>
<i>intelligence sources confirm...</i>

352
00:28:32,389 --> 00:28:36,120
<i>...that the terrorists plan to use</i>
<i>the contaminated blood as a weapon....</i>

353
00:28:36,793 --> 00:28:39,387
You know, I never thought
I'd hear myself saying this...

354
00:28:39,563 --> 00:28:42,760
...but I'm beginning to think...

355
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:45,668
...the only choice
they have is to kill these people.

356
00:28:45,869 --> 00:28:49,270
Like they did when it was drugs.
I don't know what else they can do.

357
00:28:49,439 --> 00:28:51,771
<i>--was applauded</i>
<i>by lawmakers in the state capital.</i>

358
00:28:51,942 --> 00:28:54,604
<i>The Department of Health</i>
<i>asks citizens with information...</i>

359
00:28:54,778 --> 00:28:58,339
<i>...regarding the activities of this group</i>
<i>to contact the home guard...</i>

360
00:28:58,548 --> 00:29:00,607
<i>...or call Operation Helping Hand.</i>

361
00:29:00,784 --> 00:29:02,308
<i>On the international scene....</i>

362
00:29:02,486 --> 00:29:04,386
<i>I know you like her...</i>

363
00:29:04,554 --> 00:29:07,352
...otherwise, you wouldn't bother
to be so mean to her.

364
00:29:07,524 --> 00:29:09,549
I remember you used to try
that with my mom...

365
00:29:09,726 --> 00:29:11,421
...when you were going out with her.

366
00:29:11,595 --> 00:29:15,554
At least in those days,
you used to have a little privacy.

367
00:29:15,732 --> 00:29:19,759
Fine. I'll turn myself into the state.

368
00:29:19,936 --> 00:29:23,372
You meet any hot social workers,
you get their number.

369
00:29:24,141 --> 00:29:26,302
Go downstairs.

370
00:29:31,415 --> 00:29:32,473
-Torch?
-Yeah?

371
00:29:33,917 --> 00:29:36,249
Was my mom a good cook?

372
00:29:37,254 --> 00:29:38,744
Yeah, Willie, she was a good cook.

373
00:29:38,922 --> 00:29:42,016
And she could grow stuff too,
couldn't she?

374
00:29:42,192 --> 00:29:44,092
Radishes and stuff.

375
00:29:44,261 --> 00:29:46,752
I remember I used to help her water.

376
00:29:46,963 --> 00:29:50,160
Think we could start
growing stuff again, Torch?

377
00:29:50,367 --> 00:29:51,994
Torch?

378
00:29:53,503 --> 00:29:55,528
She's not gonna get
any more dead, man.

379
00:29:55,706 --> 00:29:57,901
-You watch your mouth!
-Look.

380
00:29:58,809 --> 00:30:03,712
She was my mom.
I can talk about her if I want to.

381
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:08,010
She's not gonna get any more dead
if you sleep where it's clean.

382
00:30:08,185 --> 00:30:13,953
Or eat regular food like a person,
or be nice to some girl you like.

383
00:30:14,257 --> 00:30:16,691
She's as dead as she's gonna get.

384
00:30:18,195 --> 00:30:20,755
I hope you flunk your English test.

385
00:30:20,931 --> 00:30:25,231
Too late, it was yesterday.
And I aced it.

386
00:30:33,610 --> 00:30:35,407
<i>Laurie, it was unbelievable.</i>

387
00:30:35,579 --> 00:30:37,672
The way these people
have been treated.

388
00:30:37,881 --> 00:30:40,372
When they get to quarantine,
they put tattoos on them.

389
00:30:40,550 --> 00:30:43,576
These big P's for positive,
so they can track them down with radar.

390
00:30:43,787 --> 00:30:45,812
Do you swear to me,
that when this is over...

391
00:30:45,989 --> 00:30:49,322
...you'll forget
this entire thing ever existed?

392
00:30:49,493 --> 00:30:51,427
I mean it, Blue.

393
00:30:51,595 --> 00:30:53,119
This is it.

394
00:30:53,530 --> 00:30:55,225
Right up that ramp.

395
00:30:55,599 --> 00:30:56,930
Come on.

396
00:30:57,134 --> 00:31:01,537
We fix cars here, ma'am.
You want a doctor, find a hospital.

397
00:31:01,705 --> 00:31:05,471
They know me. I was here last night.
I know what's behind that curtain.

398
00:31:05,742 --> 00:31:08,404
If you'll excuse me,
I have a lot of work to do.

399
00:31:08,578 --> 00:31:10,603
My friend needs somebody
to give her the test.

400
00:31:10,781 --> 00:31:13,147
We don't wanna go back
to Helping Hand.

401
00:31:13,316 --> 00:31:15,181
-Boss!
-I think maybe we should just go.

402
00:31:15,352 --> 00:31:18,480
-No.
-Hey!

403
00:31:18,655 --> 00:31:22,887
You wouldn't believe this, Laurie.
Beds, medicine, hospital stuff.

404
00:31:25,929 --> 00:31:27,794
What is this?

405
00:31:28,932 --> 00:31:30,399
We crossed the continental divide
of weirdness.

406
00:31:31,668 --> 00:31:33,465
You wanna take the test?

407
00:31:33,637 --> 00:31:36,037
Be under the 4th Street bridge
in an hour.

408
00:31:36,506 --> 00:31:37,939
Just the two of you.

409
00:31:38,275 --> 00:31:41,870
Anybody else shows up,
this doesn't happen.

410
00:31:45,482 --> 00:31:46,972
No.

411
00:31:47,384 --> 00:31:48,408
-No.
-Come on.

412
00:31:48,585 --> 00:31:49,882
-No.
-Come on.

413
00:31:50,187 --> 00:31:55,420
So who's this person
who's such a big emergency?

414
00:31:55,625 --> 00:31:59,026
Nobody.
Just somebody I met in the park.

415
00:32:00,697 --> 00:32:04,724
All right, now, you just hold real steady.

416
00:32:06,236 --> 00:32:09,000
Are you sure this is sanitary out here?

417
00:32:09,172 --> 00:32:11,936
You mean without any magazines
and a waiting room?

418
00:32:12,108 --> 00:32:14,440
In the Helping Hand clinic
where I work...

419
00:32:14,611 --> 00:32:17,239
...we got all the white tile
you could ever want.

420
00:32:17,447 --> 00:32:19,779
And I wouldn't go there
to get my nose blown.

421
00:32:19,983 --> 00:32:21,177
You work for them?

422
00:32:21,351 --> 00:32:24,752
Not every double agent
wears a trench coat.

423
00:32:26,256 --> 00:32:27,280
Somebody's coming.

424
00:32:27,924 --> 00:32:31,451
Not to worry,
just our friendly mobile testing unit.

425
00:32:31,661 --> 00:32:33,629
Instant results around the clock.

426
00:32:33,797 --> 00:32:36,766
I don't know if I'm ready for instant.

427
00:32:44,274 --> 00:32:45,400
Hi.

428
00:32:49,579 --> 00:32:51,740
The keys are in the cab, Anna.

429
00:32:51,915 --> 00:32:54,577
The equipment's running a little hot,
should be okay, though.

430
00:32:54,751 --> 00:32:56,048
What's his problem?

431
00:32:56,753 --> 00:32:58,846
Who cares?

432
00:33:06,096 --> 00:33:08,826
Torch. Hey, Torch,
what is your problem?

433
00:33:08,999 --> 00:33:12,162
Hey, I ain't got no problem
except for you yelling at me.

434
00:33:12,335 --> 00:33:14,326
I don't get this.

435
00:33:14,604 --> 00:33:16,572
What we went through last night,
and then--

436
00:33:16,773 --> 00:33:19,503
Did I get you pregnant and leave you
by the roadside somewhere?

437
00:33:19,676 --> 00:33:22,611
-I don't remember this.
-I am not talking about marriage.

438
00:33:22,779 --> 00:33:24,906
I'm talking about saying hello.

439
00:33:26,616 --> 00:33:28,015
Hello.

440
00:33:29,619 --> 00:33:30,847
I'm okay.

441
00:33:31,154 --> 00:33:35,022
Blue, I'm okay. She said
it's just allergies or something.

442
00:33:36,393 --> 00:33:38,554
Oh, God.

443
00:33:44,534 --> 00:33:46,559
Let's get out of here.
My mom's on nightshift.

444
00:33:46,736 --> 00:33:50,502
-We got some major celebrating to do.
-Thank you, guys, so much. Thank you.

445
00:33:50,674 --> 00:33:53,404
-Does it feel good to say I told you so.
-Blue.

446
00:33:54,210 --> 00:33:56,144
Blue.

447
00:33:56,313 --> 00:33:58,907
-What?
-Look....

448
00:33:59,215 --> 00:34:03,242
Just because he's messed up
doesn't mean we don't need the help.

449
00:34:03,420 --> 00:34:06,548
Is there any way somebody
could get ahold of you, ever?

450
00:34:06,723 --> 00:34:09,624
What do you mean, in case Mr. Hero
needs someone to impress?

451
00:34:09,793 --> 00:34:11,488
Blue.

452
00:34:15,498 --> 00:34:18,365
You take care of yourself, okay?

453
00:34:40,457 --> 00:34:43,255
Blue? Aren't you gonna show up
to your own party?

454
00:34:43,426 --> 00:34:45,587
You want a beer or something?

455
00:35:07,450 --> 00:35:09,315
Fuck.

456
00:35:52,595 --> 00:35:55,496
Hey, what are you doing in here?
People are starting to wonder.

457
00:35:56,599 --> 00:35:58,396
What's that thing on your head?

458
00:36:03,640 --> 00:36:06,734
I guess you think everything in the world
is just wonderful now.

459
00:36:15,719 --> 00:36:17,380
Fine.

460
00:36:17,554 --> 00:36:21,513
Maybe it's all true. Maybe all this
terrible stuff is actually happening.

461
00:36:21,691 --> 00:36:25,149
But, Blue, you're crazy if you think
that there is one thing...

462
00:36:25,328 --> 00:36:28,024
...that you or I or anybody else
can do about it.

463
00:36:28,565 --> 00:36:30,260
I guess I don't see it that way.

464
00:36:30,433 --> 00:36:34,563
Just don't do anything stupid, okay?
Please? I mean, really.

465
00:36:34,738 --> 00:36:36,330
Hey, you guys, you gotta hear this.

466
00:36:36,539 --> 00:36:39,133
<i>The mobilization of the forces</i>
<i>that have been on alert...</i>

467
00:36:39,309 --> 00:36:41,106
<i>...since yesterday's</i>
<i>unprovoked attack.</i>

468
00:36:41,277 --> 00:36:46,738
<i>We have acted decisively</i>
<i>and we have acted justly.</i>

469
00:36:47,650 --> 00:36:50,585
<i>We have acted because we cannot...</i>

470
00:36:50,787 --> 00:36:54,780
<i>...must not allow tyranny</i>
<i>to cast its evil shadow.</i>

471
00:36:55,091 --> 00:37:01,621
<i>We have acted because</i>
<i>as long as one man is not free...</i>

472
00:37:03,166 --> 00:37:05,259
<i>...no man is free.</i>

473
00:37:05,435 --> 00:37:08,666
-Yeah. All right, yeah.
-Yeah.

474
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:39,534
Hey, Blue.

475
00:37:48,845 --> 00:37:50,938
We could use an extra hand tonight.

476
00:37:51,114 --> 00:37:53,446
What, the regular girl call in sick?

477
00:37:54,684 --> 00:37:56,743
Look, I'm sorry.

478
00:37:58,121 --> 00:38:00,817
What do you want?
You want me to eat dirt, I'll eat dirt.

479
00:38:01,024 --> 00:38:02,389
That would be nice.

480
00:38:17,240 --> 00:38:18,639
Chicken.

481
00:38:58,081 --> 00:38:59,446
Laurie.

482
00:39:01,584 --> 00:39:04,280
-Where's Blue?
-I don't know.

483
00:39:23,273 --> 00:39:24,831
Hey.

484
00:39:25,308 --> 00:39:26,332
Oh, hi, man.

485
00:39:29,579 --> 00:39:31,103
Use them, okay?

486
00:39:31,314 --> 00:39:34,442
The bleach, the needles, everything.

487
00:39:37,654 --> 00:39:41,488
-Got anybody I could use this with?
-Not my department.

488
00:39:48,398 --> 00:39:49,990
Where the hell you been, man?

489
00:39:51,834 --> 00:39:54,894
-Hey, Willie.
-Hey, Blue.

490
00:40:05,748 --> 00:40:08,012
-There you are.
-Hi.

491
00:40:08,184 --> 00:40:09,617
Hey.

492
00:40:09,786 --> 00:40:14,985
Listen, Laurie, I need some help,
and I don't know who else to turn to.

493
00:40:15,591 --> 00:40:17,286
Help with what?

494
00:40:17,460 --> 00:40:19,155
Is Blue having some sort of problem?

495
00:40:20,630 --> 00:40:23,030
Why would you think
that she was having a problem?

496
00:40:24,334 --> 00:40:26,495
Well, she seems so down these days,
you know?

497
00:40:26,669 --> 00:40:30,435
That's too bad,
because there's so much to be up about.

498
00:40:30,640 --> 00:40:32,574
Things are really starting
to come together.

499
00:40:32,742 --> 00:40:36,075
She's fine. She's perfectly happy.

500
00:40:36,245 --> 00:40:38,543
Hey, Laurie, how about this--?

501
00:40:42,585 --> 00:40:45,281
But Blue
is having some sort of problem.

502
00:40:45,455 --> 00:40:48,288
When the cops get wind of it...

503
00:40:48,458 --> 00:40:51,291
...you're gonna wish real hard
that you wouldn't let someone...

504
00:40:51,494 --> 00:40:55,863
...who's Blue's friend get her out of it
before it was too late.

505
00:40:56,833 --> 00:40:58,460
Blue's fine.

506
00:40:59,902 --> 00:41:01,699
Okay.

507
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:13,742
Can you believe that somebody
would name their kid Drusilla?

508
00:41:14,050 --> 00:41:16,814
-Criminal.
-It was after some aunt of my dad's.

509
00:41:16,986 --> 00:41:20,547
But my mom turned it
to Dru pretty fast.

510
00:41:21,290 --> 00:41:23,349
Bucky couldn't even say that.

511
00:41:23,526 --> 00:41:26,256
All he could say was Blue.

512
00:41:26,796 --> 00:41:29,196
I guess it kind of stuck.

513
00:41:34,904 --> 00:41:37,099
Hey, it's your turn.

514
00:41:39,075 --> 00:41:41,635
-What's this for?
-For your face.

515
00:41:41,811 --> 00:41:44,143
Oh, yeah.

516
00:41:45,081 --> 00:41:47,845
I got mine from Willie's mom.

517
00:41:48,117 --> 00:41:51,314
She hated her own name. Ellen.

518
00:41:51,487 --> 00:41:56,424
She said it sounded like someone
who won prizes for their handwriting.

519
00:41:57,760 --> 00:42:01,628
I kind of liked it, but I said, ''Okay, we
should make up names for each other...

520
00:42:01,798 --> 00:42:04,562
...only you had to take the name
you got given, period.

521
00:42:04,734 --> 00:42:06,759
No going back.''

522
00:42:10,306 --> 00:42:14,800
We-- We wrote our names on the inside
of matchbook covers, right?

523
00:42:15,144 --> 00:42:19,342
We switched,
counted to three and looked.

524
00:42:21,517 --> 00:42:26,545
I don't know where she came up with it,
but she put down Torch.

525
00:42:28,191 --> 00:42:30,386
I put down Ellen.

526
00:42:31,527 --> 00:42:34,462
We nearly killed each other
on the spot.

527
00:42:40,136 --> 00:42:42,331
What was your name before?

528
00:42:45,741 --> 00:42:48,608
I can't say.
That was another part of the deal.

529
00:42:48,778 --> 00:42:51,178
Who was Willie's father?

530
00:42:51,514 --> 00:42:53,209
She got pregnant on the job.

531
00:42:53,382 --> 00:42:57,284
You know, she said meeting me
got her out of the trade...

532
00:42:57,453 --> 00:43:00,786
...but Willie pretty much talked her
out of it before I ever came along.

533
00:43:01,057 --> 00:43:03,150
What happened to her?

534
00:43:08,531 --> 00:43:11,591
Sure. You don't have to tell me
if you don't want to.

535
00:43:16,639 --> 00:43:18,607
Well....

536
00:43:19,408 --> 00:43:21,638
It was in the beginning...

537
00:43:23,312 --> 00:43:25,940
...when they first started
taking people away.

538
00:43:26,716 --> 00:43:30,152
The whole world was sticking
its fucking head in the sand.

539
00:43:30,353 --> 00:43:32,753
Oh, but not her, no.

540
00:43:32,922 --> 00:43:37,484
She had this crazy idea that sick people
were supposed to get taken care of.

541
00:43:37,660 --> 00:43:43,155
She started making trouble,
driving people up the wall.

542
00:43:45,034 --> 00:43:46,797
They wanted her bad.

543
00:43:47,503 --> 00:43:49,528
When they raided this place
we were staying...

544
00:43:49,705 --> 00:43:53,471
...she was the only one they took.
The troublemaker.

545
00:43:59,015 --> 00:44:03,247
One morning, Willie wakes up,
and she's just not there anymore.

546
00:44:05,188 --> 00:44:06,382
The way I heard it...

547
00:44:06,556 --> 00:44:10,151
...when she came up positive,
they broke out the champagne.

548
00:44:10,359 --> 00:44:13,294
It meant this time,
they had her for good.

549
00:44:14,397 --> 00:44:15,796
No paperwork.

550
00:44:16,432 --> 00:44:19,026
They were very interested
in what she could tell them...

551
00:44:19,202 --> 00:44:22,399
...about her secret terrorist network.

552
00:44:22,738 --> 00:44:25,172
And the doctors who were present...

553
00:44:25,374 --> 00:44:32,007
...knew how to be effective
in their interrogation.

554
00:44:33,416 --> 00:44:35,111
Because....

555
00:44:35,718 --> 00:44:38,186
Because what the--
What the blood test also showed...

556
00:44:38,354 --> 00:44:41,585
...was that the subject...

557
00:44:41,757 --> 00:44:45,818
...was somewhere between
three- and five-months pregnant.

558
00:44:47,430 --> 00:44:50,661
Patients in the quarantine tried
to take care of her...

559
00:44:50,833 --> 00:44:53,529
...but after a beating like that....

560
00:44:54,670 --> 00:44:55,898
Was it your baby?

561
00:46:52,521 --> 00:46:54,546
Where did you toss Willie's bag?

562
00:47:11,006 --> 00:47:12,701
Can you feel anything with that on?

563
00:47:13,442 --> 00:47:14,636
Enough.

564
00:47:26,522 --> 00:47:29,582
Did you know she was sick
before she got caught?

565
00:47:31,026 --> 00:47:33,153
They call it denial.

566
00:47:38,634 --> 00:47:40,124
Sorry.

567
00:47:41,170 --> 00:47:42,728
Sorry.

568
00:47:47,042 --> 00:47:49,203
Have you ever taken the test?

569
00:47:51,547 --> 00:47:53,879
Everybody's got these calendars
in their head.

570
00:47:54,049 --> 00:47:56,711
So you find out you got five years.
So, what do you do?

571
00:47:57,019 --> 00:47:59,078
Start X-ing off the days
in your datebook?

572
00:47:59,255 --> 00:48:02,418
Take the necessary precautions
and you go from there.

573
00:48:02,591 --> 00:48:04,957
All that stuff they say
about nothing being safe--

574
00:48:05,127 --> 00:48:09,188
Hey, Torch.
You got anything for breakfast?

575
00:48:09,398 --> 00:48:12,196
-Where's my shirt?
-Hey, you ever heard of knocking, man?

576
00:48:13,035 --> 00:48:14,832
I'm starving, man.

577
00:48:15,004 --> 00:48:17,939
We'll pick up a donut
on the way to the bus.

578
00:48:18,107 --> 00:48:21,133
He's a growing boy.
You can't give him donuts for breakfast.

579
00:48:21,310 --> 00:48:24,302
I get him the jelly kind,
it's got fruit inside.

580
00:48:24,513 --> 00:48:27,175
Tell me you didn't actually say that.

581
00:48:28,517 --> 00:48:31,042
Well, don't wake me till Christmas.

582
00:48:31,253 --> 00:48:34,051
No, no, no. You gotta get home
before your brother gets up.

583
00:48:34,223 --> 00:48:38,956
-He can go to hell.
-Very bad attitude.

584
00:48:39,128 --> 00:48:41,653
-You got a cover to keep now.
-I do?

585
00:48:41,931 --> 00:48:46,231
Please, no bright-eyed idealism
before I get my coffee, all right?

586
00:48:47,336 --> 00:48:50,703
Morning, guys.
Do you need a toothbrush, Blue?

587
00:48:51,106 --> 00:48:55,167
-Don't worry, it's brand-new.
-Thanks.

588
00:49:02,418 --> 00:49:03,510
Torch?

589
00:49:05,454 --> 00:49:07,445
Come on, man.

590
00:50:20,729 --> 00:50:23,254
Peace for all, little brother.

591
00:51:56,992 --> 00:51:59,460
See, it's not so bad.

592
00:52:04,033 --> 00:52:05,796
Nice and slow.

593
00:52:07,536 --> 00:52:09,800
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

594
00:52:11,006 --> 00:52:14,203
It's okay. Okay--

595
00:52:17,146 --> 00:52:18,704
Ma.

596
00:52:20,182 --> 00:52:22,946
-Ma.
-You take it easy, I'll be right back.

597
00:52:24,286 --> 00:52:26,447
Where are you, Ma?

598
00:52:26,822 --> 00:52:28,449
Ma.

599
00:52:28,624 --> 00:52:30,114
Ma.

600
00:52:30,759 --> 00:52:34,160
-Ma.
-I'm right here.

601
00:52:42,004 --> 00:52:44,802
I guess you couldn't get Dad
to come, huh?

602
00:52:49,912 --> 00:52:52,210
No, no, he's here,
he's right over there.

603
00:53:02,858 --> 00:53:04,792
He's coming.

604
00:53:11,333 --> 00:53:13,164
Hey.

605
00:53:13,669 --> 00:53:16,866
-It's Russell.
-Russell.

606
00:53:17,573 --> 00:53:19,370
Hey, Dad.

607
00:53:22,845 --> 00:53:24,574
You don't still hate me, huh?

608
00:53:25,714 --> 00:53:28,581
No, I don't hate you, Russ.

609
00:53:37,926 --> 00:53:40,121
I love you, Russell.

610
00:53:41,997 --> 00:53:45,592
I love you too, Dad. I love you, Dad.

611
00:53:53,408 --> 00:53:55,876
So why haven't I heard
any hot details yet?

612
00:53:56,178 --> 00:53:57,577
Because there haven't been any.

613
00:53:57,746 --> 00:54:01,147
Every night with this guy for a month
and I'm supposed to believe that?

614
00:54:01,316 --> 00:54:03,580
-That's right.
-Well, I don't.

615
00:54:03,752 --> 00:54:05,617
Laurie, when have I ever lied to you?

616
00:54:05,821 --> 00:54:08,085
Fifth grade. Scott Berkowitz.

617
00:54:08,290 --> 00:54:11,191
You promised me that you would
never ever mention that again.

618
00:54:11,360 --> 00:54:14,921
How could you do it, Blue?
He smelled like pastrami farts.

619
00:54:15,097 --> 00:54:17,725
Actually, it was more like corned beef
when you got up close.

620
00:54:17,900 --> 00:54:19,333
Stop.

621
00:54:19,768 --> 00:54:24,705
-What are you looking at my watch for?
-Just wanted to see what time it was.

622
00:54:24,907 --> 00:54:26,431
Well, what's your hurry?

623
00:54:26,642 --> 00:54:29,611
We haven't had a normal conversation
in a million years.

624
00:54:29,778 --> 00:54:31,143
I mean, come on.

625
00:54:31,313 --> 00:54:34,840
Why can't you put up posters
a half an hour later?

626
00:54:37,786 --> 00:54:41,153
We're not exactly
putting up posters today.

627
00:54:41,924 --> 00:54:44,893
-Then what are you doing?
-You don't want to know.

628
00:54:45,227 --> 00:54:47,491
Don't tell me what I don't want.

629
00:54:47,663 --> 00:54:50,257
If I got caught,
you'd be better off not knowing.

630
00:54:50,432 --> 00:54:51,763
Just tell me.

631
00:54:52,701 --> 00:54:56,831
I miss talking to you, Blue.
I miss telling each other everything.

632
00:55:00,175 --> 00:55:03,110
We found out that there's
this Helping Hand clinic in New Jersey...

633
00:55:03,278 --> 00:55:04,643
...that's closing tonight.

634
00:55:04,813 --> 00:55:08,271
And they're shipping everybody
that they're holding to quarantine.

635
00:55:08,483 --> 00:55:10,849
And you're gonna rescue them
on the way?

636
00:55:11,019 --> 00:55:14,216
Yeah, we're gonna get them
into safe houses.

637
00:55:14,590 --> 00:55:18,424
These people you're rescuing them from,
they don't have guns?

638
00:55:21,330 --> 00:55:22,797
Blue.

639
00:55:24,933 --> 00:55:26,662
We have guns too, Laurie.

640
00:55:27,102 --> 00:55:30,196
Blue, don't go, okay?

641
00:55:30,372 --> 00:55:32,840
Really, don't go. Just, don't do it.

642
00:55:33,141 --> 00:55:35,268
It's 70 people.

643
00:55:35,444 --> 00:55:37,776
They're gonna lock them up
and starve them.

644
00:55:39,448 --> 00:55:43,043
I just don't think, you know,
if this guy really loved you...

645
00:55:43,218 --> 00:55:46,312
...he wouldn't want you
to be in all this danger all the time.

646
00:55:46,488 --> 00:55:48,786
It's not about him.

647
00:55:50,392 --> 00:55:51,723
It's just....

648
00:55:51,927 --> 00:55:55,522
I don't know, you get put on this planet
and what do you do with that?

649
00:55:55,697 --> 00:55:56,823
So, what are you saying?

650
00:55:57,132 --> 00:56:00,226
You telling me I'm fucked up
because I wanna have a normal life?

651
00:56:00,402 --> 00:56:03,394
-I'm not saying that, you know it.
-No, I don't.

652
00:56:05,207 --> 00:56:07,607
I don't know anything.

653
00:56:12,648 --> 00:56:18,143
-I have no intentions of getting killed.
-Nobody ever does.

654
00:56:26,695 --> 00:56:28,629
Well, I gotta go.

655
00:56:32,134 --> 00:56:33,829
So go.

656
00:56:36,605 --> 00:56:38,630
Call you tomorrow morning?

657
00:56:39,474 --> 00:56:41,408
You're gonna be late.

658
00:56:49,718 --> 00:56:51,549
Go on.

659
00:56:59,995 --> 00:57:01,758
Truck's coming in a little early, Torch.

660
00:57:01,930 --> 00:57:03,295
You'd better hurry up.

661
00:57:03,465 --> 00:57:05,592
-No escort?
<i>-Not that I can see.</i>

662
00:57:05,767 --> 00:57:08,497
<i>And I can see all the way to Canada.</i>

663
00:57:08,670 --> 00:57:10,729
You got enough people down there
for this?

664
00:57:11,406 --> 00:57:13,840
We got everybody we know
out here, Willie.

665
00:57:14,109 --> 00:57:16,134
Now you stay low.

666
00:57:25,187 --> 00:57:26,518
Hold it.

667
00:57:40,135 --> 00:57:42,228
-Nobody move.
-You rat.

668
00:57:44,439 --> 00:57:46,464
Now,
if you kindly drop your weapons...

669
00:57:46,641 --> 00:57:50,338
...and put your hands in the air. Now.

670
00:57:50,812 --> 00:57:53,713
Put it in the truck. Do it.

671
00:57:58,553 --> 00:58:00,350
-Get it open!
-It's not holding.

672
00:58:00,522 --> 00:58:03,355
-Come on.
-Kick it open.

673
00:58:05,260 --> 00:58:07,558
Let's go. Let's go, let's go,
let's go, let's go.

674
00:58:10,665 --> 00:58:13,691
We did it. We fucking did it, come on.

675
00:58:23,378 --> 00:58:26,779
-Hands on the truck, come on.
-Where are you, man? I can't see you.

676
00:58:33,755 --> 00:58:37,885
<i>Wherever you are, get out</i>
<i>to Pearl Street, you'll be in the clear.</i>

677
00:58:38,827 --> 00:58:42,160
-What is it?
-My walkie.

678
00:58:44,166 --> 00:58:45,793
Check under the bridge.

679
00:58:54,276 --> 00:58:55,937
<i>Cancel that about Pearl Street.</i>

680
00:58:56,111 --> 00:58:59,205
<i>It's starting to look like</i>
<i>a cop convention down there.</i>

681
00:58:59,381 --> 00:59:01,975
<i>-If you're holed up somewhere, sit tight.</i>
-Shut up.

682
00:59:02,150 --> 00:59:03,674
It's a kid.

683
00:59:03,852 --> 00:59:05,945
It's not a kid, man, it's a sniper.

684
00:59:06,121 --> 00:59:09,454
<i>Torch, where are you?</i>
<i>Come on, Torch, answer me.</i>

685
00:59:09,624 --> 00:59:13,617
<i>I can't see you.</i>
<i>What's going on down there?</i>

686
00:59:13,795 --> 00:59:16,764
There he is, captain.
I got a clear shot at his ass.

687
00:59:19,468 --> 00:59:21,561
-No!
-Torch!

688
00:59:24,206 --> 00:59:26,538
Willie!

689
00:59:30,345 --> 00:59:32,905
-No!
-Give me your fucking hands.

690
00:59:33,181 --> 00:59:36,241
No! Willie!

691
00:59:37,185 --> 00:59:40,484
Willie! No!

692
00:59:40,655 --> 00:59:42,714
No! Get it on the radio.

693
00:59:42,891 --> 00:59:45,655
Get off-- Get off me!

694
00:59:49,164 --> 00:59:51,428
Willie!

695
00:59:57,205 --> 00:59:59,173
Bucky, come here.

696
01:00:09,451 --> 01:00:11,749
Now you know why
we had to come out here today.

697
01:00:11,953 --> 01:00:15,684
But it's cool, man.
People make mistakes.

698
01:00:15,857 --> 01:00:19,623
Instead you'll have to keep an eye on her
now, make sure she learned her lesson.

699
01:00:19,794 --> 01:00:22,888
I can count on you for that, can't I?

700
01:00:24,132 --> 01:00:25,565
In the car.

701
01:00:39,681 --> 01:00:42,514
Oh, Willie. Oh, my God.

702
01:00:59,534 --> 01:01:01,092
Willie.

703
01:01:01,469 --> 01:01:02,993
