All right.

947
01:22:25,752 --> 01:22:29,119
I'm going
as long as you tell me one thing.

948
01:22:32,059 --> 01:22:34,653
Tell me that you don't want me here.

949
01:22:35,062 --> 01:22:38,293
No, no. For real.

950
01:22:38,465 --> 01:22:42,424
And you tell me
that you want to be alone...

951
01:22:43,337 --> 01:22:47,569
...when you're going blind
and your head is swelling up with sores?

952
01:22:47,774 --> 01:22:51,801
Tell me that you want me to be alone
when I know what's happening to you.

953
01:22:52,379 --> 01:22:57,510
I'm outside,
picking Pepsi cans out of the trash.

954
01:22:59,686 --> 01:23:02,246
I can't kiss your forehead.

955
01:23:03,824 --> 01:23:06,691
Bring you a glass of water.

956
01:23:08,462 --> 01:23:11,795
Or help you go to the bathroom
when you can't get out of bed.

957
01:23:14,167 --> 01:23:17,068
Tell me that's what you want
and I'm out the window.

958
01:23:19,573 --> 01:23:23,100
-Say it!
-All right, you tell me this.

959
01:23:24,044 --> 01:23:30,574
You tell me how I'm supposed to sit here
and watch you lose 80 pounds...

960
01:23:30,751 --> 01:23:36,280
...and spit up mucus until you die
from what I did to you.

961
01:23:36,456 --> 01:23:37,787
No.

962
01:23:41,094 --> 01:23:42,686
Oh, no.

963
01:23:45,532 --> 01:23:49,434
As messed up as this place may be,
it's still a hospital.

964
01:23:49,636 --> 01:23:53,003
-And that means pharmaceuticals.
-So?

965
01:23:53,173 --> 01:23:56,506
So if it gets too bad,
we could just go to sleep.

966
01:24:02,649 --> 01:24:04,674
A light dinner.

967
01:24:06,086 --> 01:24:08,748
Four grams of Seconal.

968
01:24:10,691 --> 01:24:12,420
Two each.

969
01:24:14,595 --> 01:24:18,087
-We just go to sleep?
-Yeah.

970
01:24:51,431 --> 01:24:53,160
It's morning.

971
01:24:54,401 --> 01:24:56,369
So?

972
01:24:58,138 --> 01:25:00,732
So right now, I'd be....

973
01:25:00,974 --> 01:25:02,635
I'd be....

974
01:25:04,277 --> 01:25:09,544
Now I'd be yelling at Willie
to get up for school.

975
01:25:09,716 --> 01:25:11,684
On a Saturday morning?

976
01:25:12,352 --> 01:25:14,377
-It's Saturday?
-Yeah.

977
01:25:15,555 --> 01:25:18,353
Somebody's supposed to meet the guy
from the printer's...

978
01:25:18,525 --> 01:25:20,220
...to pick up the deaf-mute cards.

979
01:25:20,394 --> 01:25:23,625
Doesn't matter, there's no one
to do anything with them anyway.

980
01:25:26,667 --> 01:25:28,464
There's you.

981
01:25:30,270 --> 01:25:31,760
No.

982
01:25:34,741 --> 01:25:39,235
-You've got two minutes, Blue.
-I'm not going.

983
01:25:54,428 --> 01:25:57,556
-Security!
-No!

984
01:25:57,731 --> 01:26:00,256
I got a negative in here.

985
01:26:01,468 --> 01:26:03,732
I love you, Blue.

986
01:26:09,309 --> 01:26:12,642
You'd better hurry, you just missed her.
She went down the hall.

987
01:26:49,416 --> 01:26:51,179
You know,
she would've been back by now.

988
01:26:51,351 --> 01:26:54,149
No, there might be traffic.
The bridge might be closed.

989
01:26:54,354 --> 01:26:56,151
Yes, and pigs might fly.

990
01:26:56,323 --> 01:26:58,587
You're asking me,
this whole thing's a trap.

991
01:26:58,759 --> 01:27:00,624
What are we trusting this guy for,
anyway?

992
01:27:00,794 --> 01:27:03,024
Because he's her brother.

993
01:27:04,664 --> 01:27:06,427
Come on, Simon.

994
01:27:20,747 --> 01:27:22,942
-Blue.
-Is Torch okay?

995
01:27:23,416 --> 01:27:25,145
He's okay.

996
01:27:26,219 --> 01:27:29,518
-Where are they keeping him?
-Did they tattoo him yet?

997
01:27:30,590 --> 01:27:34,253
Look, can we do
the press conference later?

998
01:27:34,761 --> 01:27:37,093
Right now, we got a lot to figure out.

999
01:27:37,264 --> 01:27:40,961
Like who's gonna go meet that guy
from the printer's up at the bridge?

1000
01:27:42,269 --> 01:27:44,760
-If you need me to do--
-What we need you to do...

1001
01:27:45,238 --> 01:27:47,604
...is go be an upstanding member
of the home guard.

1002
01:27:47,808 --> 01:27:49,708
Starting with getting to roll call
on time.

1003
01:27:49,876 --> 01:27:53,209
-They can go to hell.
-Bad attitude.

1004
01:27:53,980 --> 01:27:55,777
You've got a cover to keep.

1005
01:27:56,449 --> 01:27:58,110
We both do.

1006
01:27:58,285 --> 01:28:00,185
Well, I can handle the cards.

1007
01:28:00,387 --> 01:28:03,447
Okay.
I think we owe him 20 more dollars.

1008
01:28:03,623 --> 01:28:05,523
Do me a favor,
don't talk the guy's ear off.

1009
01:28:05,692 --> 01:28:07,956
Just get the cards and come back.

1010
01:28:08,495 --> 01:28:10,156
What most we need to figure out...

1011
01:28:10,363 --> 01:28:13,161
...is how we're gonna start
covering the clinics again.

